{"title_page": "1937\u201338 FC Basel season", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club season\n| club               = [[FC Basel]]\n| logo               = \n| season             = 1937\u201338\n| chairman           = {{Flagicon|SUI}} Emil Junker\n| mgrtitle           = Trainer /<br />Player-manager\n| manager            = {{Flagicon|SUI}} [[Fernand Jaccard]]\n| stdtitle           = Ground\n| stadium            = [[Landhof]], [[Basel]]\n| league             = [[1937\u201338 Nationalliga|Nationalliga]]\n| league result      = 4th\n| cup1               = [[Swiss Cup]]\n| cup1 result        = Round 3\n| league topscorer   = [[Numa Monnard]] (20)\n| season topscorer   = [[Numa Monnard]] (28)\n| highest attendance = 4,500 on 27 February 1938<br />vs [[Grasshopper Club Z\u00fcrich|Grasshopper Club]]<br />and on 15 May 1938<br />vs [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]\n| lowest attendance  = 2,498 on 29 August 1937<br />vs [[SC Young Fellows Juventus|Young Fellows Z\u00fcrich]]\n| average attendance = 3,499\n| prevseason         = [[1936\u201337 FC Basel season|1936\u201337]]\n| nextseason         = [[1938\u201339 FC Basel season|1938\u201339]] \n}}\n\nThe '''[[FC Basel]] 1937\u201338 season''' was the forty-fifth season since the club's foundation on 15 November 1893. FC Basel played their home games in the [[Landhof]] in the district Wettstein in Kleinbasel. Emil Junker was the club chairman and it was his second consecutive season as president.\n\n== Overview ==\n[[Fernand Jaccard]] who had taken over as first team coach during the previous season stayed on as player-manager this season. Basel played a total of 33 matches in their 1937\u201338 season. 22 of these matches were in the [[Swiss Super League|Nationalliga]], three in the [[Swiss Cup]] and eight were friendly matches. Of these eight friendlies six were played at home in the [[Landhof]], one in [[Espenmoos]] as guests to [[FC St. Gallen]] and one as guests to [[Le Havre AC]] in the north of France. Four of the friendlies were won, one was drawn and three ended with a defeat.<ref name=\"fcb-achiv-Bilanz Saison 1937/38\">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/bilanz?saison=1937/38 | title = Bilanz Saison 1937/38 | format = | work = | publisher = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | accessdate = 2019-11-16}}</ref>\n\nThe number of teams in the [[1937\u201338 Nationalliga]] was reduced by one team in comparison to the previous season. Thus 12 teams contested the championship this year, which was played as a round-robin, one team to be relegated and only one promoted from the two 1. Liga groups. Basel played an even and consistent season. 22 league games in total, 12 of them ended with a victory, three ended in a draw and the team suffered seven defeats. With 27 points Basel ended the season in fourth position, three points less than [[FC Lugano|Lugano]] who became Swiss champions. \n\nThe young forward [[Numa Monnard]], who had transferred in at the beginning of the season from [[Cantonal Neuchatel]], was the teams top goal scorer. With 20 goals he was the Nationalliga top scorer as well. He played 21 league games and in each of his first eight games he scored at least one goal. In the league match against [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne-Sport]] on 12 September 1937 he scored  a hat-trick as Basel won by four goals to nil.<ref name=\"fcb-achiv-fcb-ls 1937/38\">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=28089 | title = FC Basel - FC Lausanne-Sport 4:0 (4:0) | format = | work = | publisher = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | accessdate = 2019-11-16}}</ref> In total, including cup and friendlies, Monnard played 29 games for Basel, in which he netted 34 times.<ref name=\"fcb-achiv-Numa Monnard - Saison 1937/38\">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/spieler?command=spiele&id=8955&saison=1937/38 | title = Numa Monnard - Saison 1937/38 | format = | work = | publisher = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | accessdate = 2019-11-16}}</ref>\n\nIn the 1st principal round of the [[Swiss Cup]], as Basel played against lower tier FC Breite, Monard scored five times.<ref name=\"fcb-achiv-breite-fcb cup 1937/38\">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=28109 | title = FC Breite - FC Basel 2:10 (1:3) | format = | work = | publisher = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | accessdate = 2019-11-16}}</ref> In the next cup round Monard scored a hat-trick against [[AC Bellinzona|Bellinzona]]. However in the round of 16 Basel lost 0\u20131 against [[Grasshopper Club Z\u00fcrich|Grasshopper Club]], who then proceeded and eventually won the cup.<ref name=\"rsssf-Switzerland-1937/38\">{{cite web | first = | last = Erik Garin | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = | url = http://www.rsssf.com/tablesz/zwit38.html | title = Switzerland 1937/38 | format = | work = | publisher = Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation | accessdate = 2019-11-16}}</ref>\n\n== Players ==\nThe following is the list of the Basel first team squad during the season 1937\u201338. The list includes players that were in the squad the day the season started on 15 August 1937 but subsequently left the club after that date.\n\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=GK |name=[[Eug\u00e8ne de Kalbermatten]]}} \n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=GK |name=[[Fritz Glaser]]}} \n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=DF |name=[[Robert B\u00fcchi]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=DF |name=[[Louis Favre]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=DF |name=[[Ernst Grauer]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=MF |name=[[Ernst Hufschmid (footballer)|Ernst Hufschmid]]}} \n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= GER |pos=DF |name=[[Emil Hummel]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=DF |name=[[Heinz Els\u00e4sser]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=MF |name=[[August Ibach]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=MF |name=[[Fernand Jaccard]]}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=MF |name=[[Caspar Monigatti]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= FRG |pos=MF |name=[[Franz Sattler]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=MF |name=[[Fritz Schmidlin]] (I)}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=MF |name=[[Guglielmo Spadini]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=MF |name=[[Eduard Zuber]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=FW |name=[[Eduard Buser]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=FW |name=[[Numa Monnard]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=FW |name=[[Othmar Saner]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=FW |name=[[Ren\u00e9 Schaller]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=FW |name=[[Alfons Weber]] (II)}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n;Players who left the squad\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=GK |name=[[Ernst Kipfer]]}} \n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=DF |name=[[Heinrich Diethelm]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=MF |name=[[Paul Schaub]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=MF |name=[[Ferdinand Spichiger]]}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=FW |name=[[Enrico Ardizzoia]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= AUT |pos=FW |name=[[Josef Artimovicz]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= SUI |pos=FW |name=[[Maurice Dubosson]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |nat= AUT |pos=FW |name=[[Gottfried Havlicek]]}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n== Results ==\n\n=== Legend ===\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#CCCCCC|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n=== Friendly matches ===\n==== Pre- and mid-season ====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n| round      = Pre-season \n| date       = 1937\n| time       = \n| team1      = [[FC Basel|Basel]] {{flagicon|SUI}}\n| score      = 2 \u2013 2\n| report     = [