ayz", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removed unnecessary annotation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elizabeth_Taylor"}
{"title_page": "Vijaya Tahilramani", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = Hon'ble Mrs. Justice\n| name = Vijaya Tahilramani\n| honorific-suffix = \n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| office = [[Chief Justice]] of [[Madras High Court]]\n| term_start = 4 August 2018\n| term_end = 6 September 2019\n| nominator = [[Dipak Misra]]\n| appointer = [[Ram Nath Kovind]]\n| predecessor = [[Indira Banerjee]]\n| successor = \n| office2 = [[acting (law)|Acting]] [[Chief Justice]] of [[Bombay High Court]]\n| term_start2 = 5 December 2017\n| term_end2 = 3 August 2018\n| nominator2 = [[Dipak Misra]]\n| appointer2 = [[Ram Nath Kovind]]\n| predecessor2 = \n| successor2 = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1958|10|3|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Bombay]], [[Bombay State]], [[India]]\n| alma_mater = \n| death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|df=yes|Month DD, YYYY|Month DD, YYYY}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place = \n}}\n\n'''Vijaya Kamlesh Tahilramani''' is former [[Chief justice|Chief Justice]] of the [[Madras High Court]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Tahilramani to be CJ of Madras High Court |url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tahilramani-to-be-cj-of-madras-high-court/article24478604.ece |accessdate=6 August 2018 |agency=The Hindu}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/justice-vijaya-kamlesh-tahilramani-to-be-chief-justice-of-madras-high-court/articleshow/65070195.cms | title=Justice Vijaya Kamlesh Tahilramani to be chief justice of Madras high court | newspaper=[[The Times of India]] | first=A | last=Subramani | date=20 July 2018 | accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/govt-notifies-appointments-of-3-judges-to-sc-six-chief-justices-for-hcs/articleshow/65275750.cms | title=Govt notifies appointments of 3 judges to SC, six chief justices for HCs | newspaper=[[The Times of India]] | date=5 August 2018 | accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref> In 1982, V. K. Tahilramani joined the Bar. She has served as a Government Pleader and Public Prosecutor for [[Maharashtra]]. She became Acting Chief Justice of [[Bombay High Court]] on 5 December 2017.<ref>{{cite web |title=Justice VK Tahilramani Appointed As Chief Justice Of Madras High Court |url=http://www.livelaw.in/justice-vk-tahilramani-appointed-as-chief-justice-of-madras-high-court-read-notification/ |website=Live Law |accessdate=6 August 2018}}</ref> She attained fame for her judgement in Bilkis Bano case. She was the [[Chief justice]] of [[Madras High Court]] since 4 August 2018. On 21 September 2019 President [[Ram Nath Kovind]] accepted the resignation of Madras High Court Chief Justice Vijaya Kamlesh Tahilramani with effect from 6 September, when she put in her papers.\n\n== Resignation ==\nOn 28 August 2019 the collegium headed by [[Chief Justice of India]] and 4 other senior most judges of [[Supreme Court of India]] recommended the transfer of Justice Tahilramani. She requested the collegium to reconsider but her request was denied by the collegium on 5 September 2019. She submitted her resignation to the President [[Ram Nath Kovind]] on 6 September 2019 after being transferred to Meghalaya High Court by Supreme Court collegium. Her resignation letter was accepted on 21 September 2019.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/president-ram-nath-kovind-accepts-justice-vijaya-tahilramanis-resignation/article29475159.ece | title=President Ram Nath Kovind accepts Justice Vijaya Tahilramani\u2019s resignation  | date=21 September 2019 | newspaper=The Hindu | accessdate=15 November 2019 }}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tahilramani, Vijaya}}\n[[Category:21st-century Indian judges]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chief Justices of the Madras High Court]]\n[[Category:Indian women judges]]\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:Judges of the Mumbai High Court]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = Hon'ble Mrs. Justice\n| name = Vijaya Tahilramani\n| honorific-suffix = \n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| office = [[Chief Justice]] of [[Madras High Court]]\n| term_start = 4 August 2018\n| term_end = 6 September 2019\n| nominator = [[Dipak Misra]]\n| appointer = [[Ram Nath Kovind]]\n| predecessor = [[Indira Banerjee]]\n| successor = \n| office2 = [[acting (law)|Acting]] [[Chief Justice]] of [[Bombay High Court]]\n| term_start2 = 5 December 2017\n| term_end2 = 3 August 2018\n| nominator2 = [[Dipak Misra]]\n| appointer2 = [[Ram Nath Kovind]]\n| predecessor2 = \n| successor2 = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1958|10|3|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Bombay]], [[Bombay State]], [[India]]\n| alma_mater = \n| death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|df=yes|Month DD, YYYY|Month DD, YYYY}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place = \n}}\n\n'''Vijaya Kamlesh Tahilramani''' is former [[Chief justice|Chief Justice]] of the [[Madras High Court]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Tahilramani to be CJ of Madras High Court |url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tahilramani-to-be-cj-of-madras-high-court/article24478604.ece |accessdate=6 August 2018 |agency=The Hindu}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/justice-vijaya-kamlesh-tahilramani-to-be-chief-justice-of-madras-high-court/articleshow/65070195.cms | title=Justice Vijaya Kamlesh Tahilramani to be chief justice of Madras high court | newspaper=[[The Times of India]] | first=A | last=Subramani | date=20 July 2018 | accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/govt-notifies-appointments-of-3-judges-to-sc-six-chief-justices-for-hcs/articl